Write clean and maintainable code.

Rules:
- no duplicated logic
- separate concerns
- keep functions small

Folder Naming:
- use camelCase (e.g. userProfile, fontFiles, designSystem)

File Naming:
- use snake_case (e.g. user_profile, font_files, design_system)

Code Naming Conventions:
- variables and functions use camelCase (e.g. userName, getUserProfile())
- constants use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g. MAX_FILE_SIZE, API_BASE_URL)
- classes, interfaces, and components use PascalCase (e.g. UserProfile, NavigationBar)
- booleans use is, has, can, or should prefix with camelCase (e.g. isLoading, hasPermission)

General Rules:
- English only
- no spaces in names
- use descriptive, meaningful names
- keep naming consistent throughout the codebase
- structure code to be easy to read and easy to modify